1
00:00:07,705 --> 00:00:09,025
‎SAY NO TO PIRACY, SUPPORT ORIGINALS

2
00:01:37,905 --> 00:01:41,705
ADAPTED FROM XI XING’S NOVEL
<i>QUEEN CHU</i> ON QIDIAN.COM

3
00:01:46,145 --> 00:01:47,225
WANGCHENG

4
00:01:47,305 --> 00:01:49,865
Hooray!

5
00:01:49,945 --> 00:01:52,825
-Your Highness!
-Your Highness!

6
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:57,865
-Your Highness!
-The Grand Princess!

7
00:01:57,945 --> 00:02:00,505
Your Highness, we've prepared wine.

8
00:02:00,585 --> 00:02:03,225
Do me the honor.
Have some victory wine before you go.

9
00:02:04,065 --> 00:02:05,425
I appreciate it, General,

10
00:02:05,505 --> 00:02:07,625
but we must hurry to Yunzhong. No delays.

11
00:02:08,304 --> 00:02:09,265
Your Highness.

12
00:02:10,185 --> 00:02:13,625
She longs to go home.
Don't stand in her way.

13
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:19,425
Everybody, thank you for all this.

14
00:02:19,505 --> 00:02:21,305
Your Highness, take this for the journey.

15
00:02:21,385 --> 00:02:23,465
-Your Highness.
-Folks, the army will move out.

16
00:02:23,545 --> 00:02:26,185
Don't stand in their way or delay them.

17
00:02:26,265 --> 00:02:27,225
We appreciate your good intentions.

18
00:03:16,745 --> 00:03:17,985
My Lord, Mr. Deng is here.

19
00:03:22,385 --> 00:03:24,465
-Show him in.
-Yes.

20
00:03:31,425 --> 00:03:34,505
Mr. Xie, you're working at this late hour.

21
00:03:34,585 --> 00:03:36,705
You truly are a pillar of the court.

22
00:03:36,785 --> 00:03:39,025
You didn't visit me so late

23
00:03:39,105 --> 00:03:40,785
just to praise me, did you?

24
00:03:41,745 --> 00:03:43,545
I'm here to congratulate you.

25
00:03:44,745 --> 00:03:45,585
Mr. Xie,

26
00:03:46,265 --> 00:03:49,825
the battle of Wangcheng was a good one.

27
00:03:49,905 --> 00:03:51,465
What makes you say that?

28
00:03:52,505 --> 00:03:54,985
Her Highness commanded the victory.

29
00:03:55,065 --> 00:03:56,425
And of course,

30
00:03:57,225 --> 00:03:59,185
my brother fought valiantly.

31
00:03:59,265 --> 00:04:01,105
I dare not take any credit.

32
00:04:01,185 --> 00:04:03,825
Xie Yanlai escorted Her Highness

33
00:04:04,425 --> 00:04:07,385
and helped secure
the victory of Wangcheng.

34
00:04:07,985 --> 00:04:10,505
So, he's likely to take over

35
00:04:10,585 --> 00:04:12,705
the frontier troops in Yunzhong.

36
00:04:13,465 --> 00:04:14,505
Mr. Xie,

37
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:16,905
that was a clever plan.

38
00:04:20,025 --> 00:04:21,425
Have you lost your senses?

39
00:04:21,504 --> 00:04:25,385
His Majesty made Yanlai
the Imperial Guard Commander.

40
00:04:26,065 --> 00:04:27,785
How could he leave the imperial city?

41
00:04:28,385 --> 00:04:29,465
Besides,

42
00:04:30,225 --> 00:04:32,265
it won't be easy
to take over frontier troops.

43
00:04:32,345 --> 00:04:34,545
It might be hard for someone else.

44
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:36,625
But for you,

45
00:04:37,265 --> 00:04:38,585
it's a piece of cake.

46
00:04:40,505 --> 00:04:42,105
After all, your brother

47
00:04:42,185 --> 00:04:45,265
deployed the bandits
from Cangmu Stronghold to fight for him.

48
00:04:46,985 --> 00:04:49,825
I just wonder if he knows

49
00:04:50,625 --> 00:04:52,945
his connections with those bandits

50
00:04:53,025 --> 00:04:55,825
in the Wei Village.

51
00:04:55,905 --> 00:04:59,105
Mr. Deng, what's said

52
00:05:00,265 --> 00:05:02,705
can't be unsaid.

53
00:05:05,705 --> 00:05:09,065
Mr. Xie, don't be nervous.

54
00:05:09,665 --> 00:05:11,625
I'm just curious.

55
00:05:11,705 --> 00:05:15,745
Who actually set the fire
in the Wei Village?

56
00:05:16,705 --> 00:05:18,865
And why does a man

57
00:05:18,945 --> 00:05:22,385
who cares for his younger brother
refuse to see the truth?

58
00:05:22,465 --> 00:05:24,425
If you had proof,

59
00:05:24,505 --> 00:05:26,585
you could report it to His Majesty.

60
00:05:26,665 --> 00:05:28,985
Instead, you came to probe me so late.

61
00:05:29,585 --> 00:05:31,345
Let me give you some advice.

62
00:05:31,425 --> 00:05:33,105
You can't bring down my clan

63
00:05:33,185 --> 00:05:35,625
by using Xie Yanlai.

64
00:05:36,225 --> 00:05:38,185
There's a reason

65
00:05:38,265 --> 00:05:41,385
that my clan has endured for a century.

66
00:05:42,105 --> 00:05:44,985
I'm just talking about the facts.

67
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:51,705
As for your century-old authority…

68
00:05:52,585 --> 00:05:54,465
Handled properly,

69
00:05:55,545 --> 00:05:58,065
even a big tree can be uprooted.

70
00:06:04,585 --> 00:06:06,225
How interesting.

71
00:06:07,705 --> 00:06:10,345
Mr. Deng, how about

72
00:06:11,345 --> 00:06:12,865
we make a bet?

73
00:06:20,065 --> 00:06:20,905
On what?

74
00:06:20,985 --> 00:06:22,945
Tomorrow,

75
00:06:24,225 --> 00:06:26,065
we'll both plead illness to avoid court.

76
00:06:26,665 --> 00:06:29,105
-See what His Majesty will do?
-No.

77
00:06:29,185 --> 00:06:33,505
I want you to see
who the ministers will support

78
00:06:34,865 --> 00:06:36,625
and how much

79
00:06:37,785 --> 00:06:39,585
my clan matters.

80
00:06:39,665 --> 00:06:40,785
All right.

81
00:06:43,425 --> 00:06:45,025
I'll take that bet.

82
00:07:01,585 --> 00:07:03,465
The Northern Desert envoy is here.

83
00:07:04,745 --> 00:07:05,865
You promised

84
00:07:06,705 --> 00:07:09,625
that you would send troops
to help us invade Wangcheng.

85
00:07:09,705 --> 00:07:11,025
But instead of sending any troops,

86
00:07:11,105 --> 00:07:14,025
you watched our defeat and heavy losses.

87
00:07:14,105 --> 00:07:17,985
My remaining troops all died in Yunzhong!

88
00:07:18,905 --> 00:07:21,745
I wonder how you'll explain that.

89
00:07:22,505 --> 00:07:24,545
Battle conditions change rapidly.

90
00:07:25,705 --> 00:07:29,185
I did my best to let you pass through

91
00:07:29,265 --> 00:07:31,265
at great personal risk.

92
00:07:32,105 --> 00:07:33,825
How could I have foreseen everything?

93
00:07:34,865 --> 00:07:36,025
Besides,

94
00:07:36,105 --> 00:07:38,825
if your remaining troops

95
00:07:38,905 --> 00:07:40,705
died in my prefecture,

96
00:07:40,785 --> 00:07:43,345
the court would suspect and blame me.

97
00:07:44,145 --> 00:07:45,865
It wouldn't benefit me at all.

98
00:07:47,585 --> 00:07:48,905
If it makes you

99
00:07:49,505 --> 00:07:52,305
suspect my sincerity in allying with you,

100
00:07:55,265 --> 00:07:56,825
I'll be really disappointed.

101
00:08:01,865 --> 00:08:03,585
Do you think this excuse

102
00:08:04,385 --> 00:08:08,265
will justify my troops dying in vain?

103
00:08:16,905 --> 00:08:19,145
Has your king ever trusted me?

104
00:08:20,385 --> 00:08:24,145
After all, he still hasn't told me

105
00:08:25,025 --> 00:08:26,905
why he asked me to help your men

106
00:08:27,425 --> 00:08:30,945
set the fire in the Wei Village
five years ago.

107
00:08:32,705 --> 00:08:35,024
If I hadn't sent men to clear it up,

108
00:08:35,865 --> 00:08:38,264
it wouldn't have been kept
so perfectly secret.

109
00:08:39,225 --> 00:08:41,105
But now, you doubt me.

110
00:08:44,545 --> 00:08:46,625
Go back and tell your king.

111
00:08:47,185 --> 00:08:49,665
A plan succeeds through mutual trust.

112
00:08:51,025 --> 00:08:52,985
If he demands an answer on this matter,

113
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:57,105
our alliance will end here.

114
00:09:51,665 --> 00:09:53,705
Jiu, had a nightmare?

115
00:09:58,265 --> 00:10:01,265
Just now, you looked in pain.

116
00:10:03,265 --> 00:10:04,185
Nothing.

117
00:10:06,745 --> 00:10:07,785
Just a dream.

118
00:10:14,185 --> 00:10:16,065
I'm going to see my father soon.

119
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:21,345
Aren't you supposed to be happy?

120
00:10:23,345 --> 00:10:25,225
It's not that I'm not happy.

121
00:10:26,385 --> 00:10:27,745
I'm just scared.

122
00:10:29,745 --> 00:10:30,865
Of what?

123
00:10:32,345 --> 00:10:33,785
My father's illness.

124
00:10:38,825 --> 00:10:40,545
People get sick.

125
00:10:42,585 --> 00:10:45,025
Don't worry. Maybe

126
00:10:45,745 --> 00:10:50,065
by the time we arrive,
your father will have recovered.

127
00:10:53,585 --> 00:10:55,545
I hope so.

128
00:12:01,145 --> 00:12:05,545
THE GREAT BORDER GATE

129
00:12:22,905 --> 00:12:25,465
The General once said,
when you came back someday,

130
00:12:25,545 --> 00:12:26,905
he would be waiting at the city gate.

131
00:12:32,065 --> 00:12:35,185
<i>Yeah. You're the undefeated God of War.</i>

132
00:12:35,265 --> 00:12:37,545
<i>You're the esteemed Guard General.</i>

133
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:40,665
<i>But have you ever asked</i>
<i>if I wish to be a general's daughter?</i>

134
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:42,585
Since childhood,

135
00:12:43,185 --> 00:12:45,865
other girls have had parents around.
What about me?

136
00:12:45,945 --> 00:12:47,945
I've always been neglected.

137
00:12:48,705 --> 00:12:51,065
Have I ever cried or complained to you?

138
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:53,465
I've never dared
to ask you for a little concern

139
00:12:53,545 --> 00:12:54,985
because you've always been busy.

140
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:57,585
You're busy protecting frontier people.

141
00:12:57,665 --> 00:12:59,705
You're busy forging your fame.

142
00:12:59,785 --> 00:13:01,305
You're too busy

143
00:13:01,385 --> 00:13:04,745
to ask your daughter
what she really wants!

144
00:13:07,225 --> 00:13:09,905
Father, Xun and I love each other.

145
00:13:09,985 --> 00:13:11,385
What's wrong with his origin?

146
00:13:12,025 --> 00:13:13,425
If I can't marry him,

147
00:13:13,505 --> 00:13:14,905
why did you marry my mother,

148
00:13:14,985 --> 00:13:16,425
a noble young lady from far away?

149
00:13:16,505 --> 00:13:18,945
She stayed with you
and wasted her life here.

150
00:13:19,025 --> 00:13:21,425
Your mother… You have no right to judge.

151
00:13:21,505 --> 00:13:23,265
Then don't interfere with mine!

152
00:13:25,745 --> 00:13:26,905
<i>Sorry.</i>

153
00:13:27,505 --> 00:13:29,145
<i>I'm sorry, Father.</i>

154
00:13:30,385 --> 00:13:31,305
<i>Father.</i>

155
00:13:32,185 --> 00:13:33,785
I'm sorry!

156
00:14:03,785 --> 00:14:04,705
Father,

157
00:14:07,225 --> 00:14:08,625
I'm finally back.

158
00:14:08,705 --> 00:14:09,705
Good.

159
00:14:12,105 --> 00:14:13,705
Good you're back.

160
00:14:35,465 --> 00:14:37,305
When did this happen?

161
00:14:37,385 --> 00:14:38,825
How did your eyes…?

162
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:42,825
What did the Army Physician say?

163
00:14:44,585 --> 00:14:46,745
We can send for an Imperial Physician.

164
00:14:46,825 --> 00:14:48,265
You'll be cured.

165
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,905
Don't bother.

166
00:14:50,505 --> 00:14:53,145
With or without my eyesight,

167
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:56,585
I can see everything in the camp.

168
00:14:58,425 --> 00:14:59,985
It's all in my heart.

169
00:15:13,265 --> 00:15:14,625
Actually,

170
00:15:16,945 --> 00:15:19,225
after I lost my sight,

171
00:15:20,705 --> 00:15:21,905
I finally managed

172
00:15:23,265 --> 00:15:25,065
to find inner peace.

173
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:27,825
I feel I am getting old.

174
00:15:30,065 --> 00:15:31,985
I often thought of the past.

175
00:15:34,625 --> 00:15:37,105
The more I thought,
the more I felt sorry for you.

176
00:15:37,705 --> 00:15:39,305
You've grown up,

177
00:15:41,025 --> 00:15:43,985
and I've never flown kites with you.

178
00:15:45,265 --> 00:15:47,185
I even missed

179
00:15:49,385 --> 00:15:50,665
your coming-of-age ceremony.

180
00:15:52,505 --> 00:15:54,305
I still remember those words you said

181
00:15:55,425 --> 00:15:57,065
when you left here.

182
00:15:57,905 --> 00:15:59,785
In the dead of night,

183
00:16:01,825 --> 00:16:04,265
it has haunted me all this time.

184
00:16:06,545 --> 00:16:07,665
You were right.

185
00:16:08,545 --> 00:16:10,825
I've never been a good father.

186
00:16:13,505 --> 00:16:15,625
I've never asked

187
00:16:17,585 --> 00:16:19,465
what you really want.

188
00:16:20,705 --> 00:16:21,945
I have no right

189
00:16:24,385 --> 00:16:26,225
to beg for your forgiveness.

190
00:16:28,945 --> 00:16:32,345
Don't say that, Father.
I'm sorry for what I did to you.

191
00:16:33,745 --> 00:16:37,745
Father, I shouldn't have said
those harsh words.

192
00:16:39,345 --> 00:16:41,825
Five years ago, I shouldn't
have left willfully

193
00:16:41,905 --> 00:16:43,585
without even leaving you a message.

194
00:16:45,825 --> 00:16:46,825
Father,

195
00:16:49,025 --> 00:16:50,585
will you forgive me?

196
00:16:52,825 --> 00:16:55,185
I've never blamed you.

197
00:16:55,825 --> 00:16:57,265
There's nothing to forgive.

198
00:16:58,345 --> 00:17:00,425
When you're no longer so stubborn,

199
00:17:00,505 --> 00:17:02,665
it feels strange to me.

200
00:17:03,665 --> 00:17:05,224
The biggest pride

201
00:17:06,184 --> 00:17:08,305
of my life

202
00:17:09,424 --> 00:17:11,464
isn't defeating enemies,

203
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:15,265
but having a daughter

204
00:17:18,105 --> 00:17:20,545
even more stubborn than I am.

205
00:17:25,944 --> 00:17:27,785
On the day of Wangcheng victory,

206
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,465
joy overwhelmed me.

207
00:17:31,865 --> 00:17:33,265
I asked Changrong to write

208
00:17:35,545 --> 00:17:37,465
a congratulatory poem on my behalf.

209
00:17:46,225 --> 00:17:48,265
<i>My precious daughter was too confined</i>

210
00:17:48,345 --> 00:17:50,665
<i>To let her talents shine</i>

211
00:17:51,985 --> 00:17:54,225
<i>How could I not think of her?</i>

212
00:17:54,305 --> 00:17:56,625
<i>Yet she chose to temper herself</i>

213
00:17:56,705 --> 00:17:59,225
<i>She left home and achieved great deeds</i>

214
00:17:59,305 --> 00:18:01,185
<i>And her talents finally shone brightly</i>

215
00:18:01,265 --> 00:18:03,425
<i>Glorious and bright</i>

216
00:18:03,505 --> 00:18:05,945
<i>Her light reaches the whole land</i>

217
00:18:06,825 --> 00:18:09,665
Your Majesty, an urgent military report
about rewards

218
00:18:09,745 --> 00:18:11,105
came from Wangcheng.

219
00:18:11,825 --> 00:18:13,385
Without His Majesty's approval,

220
00:18:13,465 --> 00:18:15,625
Her Highness distributed rewards
on her own.

221
00:18:16,225 --> 00:18:18,105
Wasn't she overstepping her authority?

222
00:18:24,105 --> 00:18:25,785
Mr. Xie is on sick leave.

223
00:18:26,585 --> 00:18:27,665
Mr. Deng has a day off, too.

224
00:18:28,385 --> 00:18:31,225
To whom shall we send
this military report?

225
00:18:31,945 --> 00:18:34,185
Mr. Deng, of course.

226
00:18:34,785 --> 00:18:37,145
The late Emperor made him the regent.

227
00:18:37,225 --> 00:18:39,425
We can't bypass him in military affairs.

228
00:18:39,505 --> 00:18:40,905
Military affairs are urgent.

229
00:18:40,985 --> 00:18:42,865
Mr. Deng knows nothing
about warfare tactics.

230
00:18:42,945 --> 00:18:45,105
Before Mr. Xie asked for sick leave,

231
00:18:45,185 --> 00:18:47,905
he ordered that all military reports
to be sent to him.

232
00:18:49,065 --> 00:18:51,425
Mr. Deng also gave an order.

233
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:54,665
Frontier affairs must be reviewed by him.

234
00:18:55,265 --> 00:18:58,385
The Xie Clan of Gaoyang
has stood for a century.

235
00:18:58,465 --> 00:19:00,345
Oh. My memory fails me.

236
00:19:00,945 --> 00:19:02,265
How many prime ministers

237
00:19:02,345 --> 00:19:04,545
have come from their clan?

238
00:19:06,945 --> 00:19:10,305
Since the founding of our dynasty,
there have been six.

239
00:19:13,985 --> 00:19:15,545
Then send it to Mr. Xie.

240
00:19:18,025 --> 00:19:20,185
-But…
-This is ridiculous.

241
00:19:21,985 --> 00:19:23,185
Anything else?

242
00:19:23,265 --> 00:19:25,265
Then the court is dismissed.

243
00:19:25,345 --> 00:19:28,025
-We bid farewell to Your Majesty.
-We bid farewell to Your Majesty.

244
00:19:29,865 --> 00:19:31,785
XIE RESIDENCE

245
00:19:34,265 --> 00:19:35,505
Mr. Xie, have you heard?

246
00:19:35,585 --> 00:19:38,065
In today's court, we won decisively.

247
00:19:38,145 --> 00:19:40,025
I heard that old censor

248
00:19:40,105 --> 00:19:41,745
nearly fainted from anger.

249
00:19:42,665 --> 00:19:44,305
How many times have I warned you?

250
00:19:45,185 --> 00:19:47,585
You must not be so arrogant.

251
00:19:47,665 --> 00:19:49,945
Arrogance leads to misfortune.

252
00:19:50,025 --> 00:19:52,585
When people praise you
and our Xie household,

253
00:19:52,665 --> 00:19:53,825
it's hard for me to stay humble.

254
00:19:54,585 --> 00:19:55,905
I can't help feeling proud.

255
00:19:57,545 --> 00:19:58,585
Forget it.

256
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:02,265
Mr. Xie, won't you review the report?

257
00:20:03,065 --> 00:20:04,905
Send this report to Mr. Deng.

258
00:20:05,505 --> 00:20:06,945
To him?

259
00:20:07,665 --> 00:20:08,985
Won't you review it?

260
00:20:10,945 --> 00:20:14,025
No one but Mr. Deng
can review this report.

261
00:20:14,585 --> 00:20:16,305
What if he doesn't…?

262
00:20:18,865 --> 00:20:19,945
He will.

263
00:20:44,025 --> 00:20:44,905
Mr. Deng,

264
00:20:47,745 --> 00:20:49,265
you lost.

265
00:20:52,025 --> 00:20:53,025
Don't be angry.

266
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:56,665
You need patience when dealing
with Xie Yanfang.

267
00:20:57,265 --> 00:21:00,625
He got the military report,
but didn't even bother to review it.

268
00:21:01,425 --> 00:21:03,505
He's obviously humiliating me.

269
00:21:14,025 --> 00:21:14,865
This man…

270
00:21:30,065 --> 00:21:30,945
It's him.

271
00:21:32,065 --> 00:21:34,025
-Who?
-Liang Qiang.

272
00:21:34,625 --> 00:21:36,505
The Third Prince's case
involves his family.

273
00:21:36,585 --> 00:21:38,345
Xie Yanfang had him exiled.

274
00:21:41,345 --> 00:21:42,505
Very good.

275
00:21:48,505 --> 00:21:51,865
APPROVED

276
00:21:52,945 --> 00:21:54,025
Approving it already?

277
00:21:56,705 --> 00:21:58,745
Since he's Xie Yanfang's enemy,

278
00:21:59,865 --> 00:22:01,905
I'll give him some support.

279
00:22:04,185 --> 00:22:05,545
SEAL OF THE GRAND MENTOR

280
00:22:12,265 --> 00:22:13,825
IMPERIAL SEAL OF THE CHU EMPEROR

281
00:22:15,105 --> 00:22:18,385
Father. Father, are you asleep? I'm back.

282
00:22:19,705 --> 00:22:22,905
I got it. I'm still awake.
I was waiting for you.

283
00:22:29,945 --> 00:22:33,265
Father, guess what I brought back.

284
00:22:36,185 --> 00:22:38,305
Did my patrol lady

285
00:22:39,585 --> 00:22:40,945
bring back a spy?

286
00:22:46,785 --> 00:22:48,465
I brought back a rabbit.

287
00:22:49,185 --> 00:22:50,545
Well done, Zhao.

288
00:22:51,465 --> 00:22:56,465
Jiu didn't catch it for you, did he?

289
00:22:58,265 --> 00:22:59,785
No.

290
00:22:59,865 --> 00:23:02,625
Father. Look.

291
00:23:02,705 --> 00:23:05,585
This little rabbit looks like a snowball.

292
00:23:06,825 --> 00:23:08,345
Rabbits can bite.

293
00:23:09,105 --> 00:23:10,345
Don't forget.

294
00:23:10,945 --> 00:23:14,105
You got bitten when you were little
and cried for three days.

295
00:23:16,625 --> 00:23:17,625
I did?

296
00:23:19,985 --> 00:23:21,745
I don't remember at all.

297
00:23:22,465 --> 00:23:23,825
You remember almost nothing

298
00:23:25,945 --> 00:23:27,265
about your childhood.

299
00:23:34,785 --> 00:23:36,225
In your childhood,

300
00:23:37,465 --> 00:23:38,745
you were extraordinary.

301
00:23:39,465 --> 00:23:41,105
When you were born,

302
00:23:42,265 --> 00:23:43,665
the room was bathed in red light.

303
00:23:44,825 --> 00:23:46,945
A fortune teller passed by

304
00:23:47,985 --> 00:23:49,985
and was utterly shocked.

305
00:23:50,745 --> 00:23:51,865
He pointed at you and said,

306
00:23:52,985 --> 00:23:54,505
"She's blessed by heaven."

307
00:23:57,225 --> 00:23:59,945
Really? Did you

308
00:24:00,545 --> 00:24:03,185
go out again and hear
a story at the tea house?

309
00:24:03,785 --> 00:24:06,745
What happened next in the story?

310
00:24:06,825 --> 00:24:08,145
Later,

311
00:24:08,865 --> 00:24:11,065
at this girl's first birthday,

312
00:24:12,505 --> 00:24:15,625
she grabbed the Frontier Tally.

313
00:24:17,465 --> 00:24:19,305
When she was five,

314
00:24:20,505 --> 00:24:24,065
she led the servants and maids

315
00:24:24,665 --> 00:24:27,105
to use brooms as spears

316
00:24:28,945 --> 00:24:30,825
and pot lids as shields,

317
00:24:32,065 --> 00:24:36,145
and she has piled up an enemy city

318
00:24:38,105 --> 00:24:39,585
with bamboo steamers.

319
00:24:40,425 --> 00:24:41,545
She even learned

320
00:24:42,345 --> 00:24:44,545
to deploy troops.

321
00:24:44,625 --> 00:24:46,625
In the end, she captured

322
00:24:47,545 --> 00:24:51,425
the steward's three hens
that would still lay eggs.

323
00:24:56,585 --> 00:24:59,785
I don't remember that.
Was I that remarkable?

324
00:25:00,785 --> 00:25:02,545
Yes, you were.

325
00:25:03,225 --> 00:25:04,505
And the old steward

326
00:25:05,625 --> 00:25:07,425
cried for two nights.

327
00:25:18,065 --> 00:25:20,745
Father, I love the congratulatory poem

328
00:25:22,585 --> 00:25:23,905
you wrote for me.

329
00:25:25,985 --> 00:25:28,065
Let me recite it again.

330
00:25:34,025 --> 00:25:35,745
<i>My precious daughter was too confined</i>

331
00:25:37,705 --> 00:25:39,465
<i>To let her talents shine</i>

332
00:25:40,665 --> 00:25:42,345
<i>How could I not think of her?</i>

333
00:25:44,625 --> 00:25:46,385
<i>Yet she chose to temper herself</i>

334
00:25:47,465 --> 00:25:49,385
<i>She left home and achieved great deeds</i>

335
00:25:50,985 --> 00:25:52,825
<i>And her talents finally shone brightly</i>

336
00:25:55,185 --> 00:25:57,065
<i>Glorious and bright</i>

337
00:25:58,585 --> 00:26:00,385
<i>Her light reaches the whole land</i>

338
00:26:02,625 --> 00:26:05,105
Father. Father!

339
00:26:07,145 --> 00:26:10,305
Father! Army Physician!

340
00:26:11,745 --> 00:26:12,625
Father.

341
00:26:28,065 --> 00:26:29,745
When I left five years ago,

342
00:26:30,905 --> 00:26:32,585
Father could still draw bows and shoot.

343
00:26:34,825 --> 00:26:36,745
When did he fall ill?

344
00:26:38,545 --> 00:26:40,065
Let me be honest.

345
00:26:40,825 --> 00:26:44,065
Over the past two years,
the General has been growing weaker.

346
00:26:50,145 --> 00:26:53,625
Actually, whether he did or didn't disarm,

347
00:26:54,345 --> 00:26:55,905
he'd end up the same.

348
00:26:56,625 --> 00:26:58,465
He's been poisoned for three years.

349
00:26:59,425 --> 00:27:01,865
<i>You sent him those cakes yourself.</i>

350
00:27:01,945 --> 00:27:04,825
<i>From the Capital to Yunzhong,</i>

351
00:27:04,905 --> 00:27:06,145
<i>they were delivered monthly.</i>

352
00:27:06,225 --> 00:27:07,065
CHU MANSION

353
00:27:07,145 --> 00:27:09,025
<i>Chu Ling would be killed anyway.</i>

354
00:27:09,625 --> 00:27:11,345
<i>Not only by my blade,</i>

355
00:27:12,305 --> 00:27:14,225
<i>but also by his daughter's love.</i>

356
00:27:14,305 --> 00:27:15,345
<i>This is impossible.</i>

357
00:27:16,025 --> 00:27:18,825
<i>In my past life, poisoned jujube cakes</i>

358
00:27:18,905 --> 00:27:20,825
<i>were sent to my father after my wedding.</i>

359
00:27:21,745 --> 00:27:23,345
<i>But in this life, no cakes were sent.</i>

360
00:27:24,305 --> 00:27:25,905
<i>Why is Father still ill?</i>

361
00:27:27,625 --> 00:27:30,425
Do you know what happened to my father?

362
00:27:31,625 --> 00:27:33,345
I'm not sure about the reason.

363
00:27:34,705 --> 00:27:36,065
I'll make him some medicine

364
00:27:36,145 --> 00:27:38,225
for refreshment and replenishment.

365
00:27:44,105 --> 00:27:45,625
You served him for five years.

366
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:48,105
Do you know why he's fading so quickly?

367
00:27:50,505 --> 00:27:51,465
Sorry.

368
00:27:53,105 --> 00:27:54,385
I have no idea.

369
00:28:09,025 --> 00:28:10,505
In this new life,

370
00:28:13,585 --> 00:28:15,145
nothing has changed.

371
00:28:17,425 --> 00:28:19,785
For you, something has.

372
00:28:29,265 --> 00:28:32,825
Yet some regrets are inevitable.

373
00:28:41,465 --> 00:28:43,385
Everything has its destiny.

374
00:28:46,225 --> 00:28:47,345
So does a human.

375
00:28:49,385 --> 00:28:51,145
He's defended the frontier all his life,

376
00:28:52,545 --> 00:28:54,225
and people revere him.

377
00:28:54,985 --> 00:28:56,345
In the final days of his life,

378
00:28:59,585 --> 00:29:00,945
his daughter and brothers-in-arms

379
00:29:02,625 --> 00:29:03,665
keep him company.

380
00:29:05,425 --> 00:29:06,425
Perhaps,

381
00:29:07,705 --> 00:29:09,505
he isn't in that much pain.

382
00:29:12,785 --> 00:29:15,145
Even if he passes away,

383
00:29:18,225 --> 00:29:19,745
his love for you

384
00:29:21,905 --> 00:29:23,385
won't fade away.

385
00:29:24,225 --> 00:29:25,745
But he shouldn't be like this.

386
00:29:27,025 --> 00:29:28,385
He just shouldn't.

387
00:29:29,265 --> 00:29:30,945
He kills enemies at the frontier

388
00:29:32,065 --> 00:29:33,865
and protects people here.

389
00:29:36,105 --> 00:29:38,305
He has done everything
a general should do.

390
00:29:40,145 --> 00:29:42,065
He protects 200,000 soldiers

391
00:29:42,665 --> 00:29:44,945
and secures the peace of the state.

392
00:29:51,065 --> 00:29:52,065
What else do you want?

393
00:29:52,145 --> 00:29:53,865
I want him to live.

394
00:29:54,465 --> 00:29:55,865
I want him to live!

395
00:29:55,945 --> 00:29:57,505
I want him to call me "silly girl",

396
00:29:57,585 --> 00:30:00,945
make jujube cakes with me,
and teach me riding and archery!

397
00:30:02,065 --> 00:30:03,425
I want to make it up

398
00:30:04,065 --> 00:30:05,745
and do what a daughter should do.

399
00:30:08,025 --> 00:30:10,985
I want him to wait for me
to come home even if he scolds me.

400
00:30:12,265 --> 00:30:15,905
I don't want a cold memorial tablet
of the Guard General.

401
00:30:28,745 --> 00:30:31,505
GATEWAY OF CANGMU STRONGHOLD

402
00:30:38,105 --> 00:30:39,505
What's wrong, Aunt?

403
00:30:41,105 --> 00:30:42,225
Chu Ling.

404
00:30:42,305 --> 00:30:44,185
CHU LING'S LIFE BURNS LOW.
BEYOND ALL HEALING. PLEASE REPLY SOON

405
00:30:45,225 --> 00:30:46,705
He's dying.

406
00:30:51,065 --> 00:30:53,065
Aunt, you…

407
00:30:54,105 --> 00:30:55,105
Are you going to see him?

408
00:31:37,785 --> 00:31:38,705
Jiu.

409
00:31:41,065 --> 00:31:42,105
Tell me.

410
00:31:43,105 --> 00:31:44,505
What will a man think

411
00:31:45,985 --> 00:31:46,945
before he dies?

412
00:31:54,505 --> 00:31:55,905
Words left unsaid,

413
00:31:57,745 --> 00:31:59,065
promises left unfulfilled…

414
00:32:01,185 --> 00:32:02,345
Or…

415
00:32:03,465 --> 00:32:04,505
wishes that went unmet.

416
00:32:06,505 --> 00:32:08,145
What could be

417
00:32:09,985 --> 00:32:11,105
my father's wish?

418
00:32:13,185 --> 00:32:14,305
If you really want to know,

419
00:32:15,305 --> 00:32:18,745
you can ask him when he wakes up.

420
00:32:20,265 --> 00:32:22,225
Just stop torturing yourself.

421
00:32:28,665 --> 00:32:29,505
Zhao,

422
00:32:32,985 --> 00:32:35,265
you look like you did something wrong.

423
00:32:36,505 --> 00:32:38,425
Your father wouldn't like it.

424
00:32:40,105 --> 00:32:41,865
I just want to figure it out.

425
00:32:45,025 --> 00:32:46,585
What exactly went wrong

426
00:32:47,785 --> 00:32:49,985
that made me end up like this again?

427
00:32:51,585 --> 00:32:53,825
I have tried so hard.

428
00:32:53,905 --> 00:32:55,625
I have tried everything.

429
00:32:55,705 --> 00:32:57,665
Why will my father still leave me?

430
00:33:00,985 --> 00:33:03,305
Zhao, calm down.

431
00:33:03,905 --> 00:33:05,545
What else can I do?

432
00:33:05,625 --> 00:33:09,625
Tell me. What else can I do
to save my father?

433
00:33:32,585 --> 00:33:35,945
MIGHT AND RIGHT

434
00:33:48,905 --> 00:33:50,665
It still tastes a bit bland.

435
00:33:53,665 --> 00:33:55,465
He can't take Zhuyu Powder.

436
00:33:55,545 --> 00:33:57,145
He's too weak to take it now.

437
00:34:00,065 --> 00:34:02,065
Madam Ge? You…

438
00:34:03,065 --> 00:34:04,425
Why are you here?

439
00:34:06,545 --> 00:34:08,065
I'm your father's…

440
00:34:12,344 --> 00:34:13,625
old friend.

441
00:34:14,705 --> 00:34:15,784
I'm here for his final farewell.

442
00:34:23,385 --> 00:34:24,585
Who on earth are you?

443
00:35:02,505 --> 00:35:03,705
Old friend?

444
00:35:04,985 --> 00:35:06,465
What kind of friend

445
00:35:07,225 --> 00:35:09,665
would even remember his food taboos?

446
00:35:13,985 --> 00:35:15,905
She didn't fight like ordinary bandits.

447
00:35:17,025 --> 00:35:18,345
In the Wangcheng battle,

448
00:35:19,145 --> 00:35:20,705
the way she wielded twin blades

449
00:35:22,305 --> 00:35:23,145
was peculiar.

450
00:35:26,825 --> 00:35:28,625
Mu Mianhong, head of Cangmu Stronghold,

451
00:35:29,385 --> 00:35:30,905
mastered twin scimitars.

452
00:35:30,985 --> 00:35:33,825
In the first year of Tianshu
when Father suppressed them,

453
00:35:34,345 --> 00:35:35,545
she jumped off a cliff and died.

454
00:35:37,665 --> 00:35:39,425
Could she be…?

455
00:35:43,425 --> 00:35:44,625
Mu Mianhong.

456
00:35:57,545 --> 00:36:00,945
General, this is our new maidservant.

457
00:36:01,025 --> 00:36:02,505
She can't speak,

458
00:36:02,585 --> 00:36:06,105
but she's good at decoction and soup.

459
00:36:07,865 --> 00:36:08,905
Thanks for your work.

460
00:36:55,905 --> 00:36:57,145
Thank you.

461
00:37:55,185 --> 00:37:56,825
WE SWEAR THIS LOVE AND MATRIMONY
BEFORE HEAVEN, EARTH AND OUR ANCESTORS

462
00:37:56,905 --> 00:37:58,905
BREAK THIS OATH AND WE BE CURSED
BY CHU LING, MU MIANHONG

463
00:38:00,985 --> 00:38:02,985
<i>Do you like this kind of father?</i>

464
00:38:03,705 --> 00:38:04,905
No?

465
00:38:06,345 --> 00:38:07,185
Why?

466
00:38:07,265 --> 00:38:09,425
Because he's a hero to others.

467
00:38:09,945 --> 00:38:11,865
He's a hero to people in Yunzhong.

468
00:38:12,545 --> 00:38:15,785
But I want him to be an ordinary father.

469
00:38:16,745 --> 00:38:20,265
He would carve wooden dolls for me,
watch fireworks with me,

470
00:38:21,105 --> 00:38:23,305
give me pretty braids,

471
00:38:24,825 --> 00:38:28,305
and be there with me
for every important moment.

472
00:38:29,545 --> 00:38:30,545
But actually…

473
00:38:31,385 --> 00:38:32,505
none of this happened.

474
00:38:34,105 --> 00:38:34,945
What about…

475
00:38:37,705 --> 00:38:38,865
your mother?

476
00:38:42,985 --> 00:38:45,345
Could Father have been lying all along?

477
00:38:46,705 --> 00:38:47,865
My mother is…

478
00:38:49,905 --> 00:38:50,745
It can't be.

479
00:39:04,465 --> 00:39:06,705
JOY AND HEALTH FOREVER

480
00:39:09,185 --> 00:39:10,225
Zhao.

481
00:39:13,025 --> 00:39:14,345
Zhao.

